Package edu.uky.cs.nil.sabre.comp

Class CompiledProblem

java.lang.Object
edu.uky.cs.nil.sabre.Problem
edu.uky.cs.nil.sabre.comp.CompiledProblem
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class CompiledProblem extends Problem
A compiled problem is a problem which has been pre-processed so that its fluents are compiled fluents, so that its events are compiled events, and so that it defines a full a state state. Various compilers produce different kinds of compiled problems, such as the grounder, fluent explicitizer, simplifier, and action shuffler.
Author:
Stephen G. Ware

    • getFluent

      public CompiledFluent getFluent(Signature signature)
      Description copied from class: Problem
      Returns a fluent defined in this problem based on the given signature. The signature does not need to match a fluent explicitly defined in this problem; it can match a fluent implicitly defined by a template. Any types and entities in the signature will be replaced with types and entities of the same name in this problem's universe, if they exist.
      Overrides:
      getFluent in class Problem
      Parameters:
      signature - the signature of the fluent to find
      Returns:
      the defined fluent

    • getFluent

      public CompiledFluent getFluent(Fluent fluent)
      Returns a compiled fluent defined in this problem based on a given fluent, which does not need to be compiled and does not need to be from this problem. The returned fluent will have the same characters and signature as the given fluent, but all of its elements will be elements defined in this problem.
      Parameters:
      fluent - a fluent whose characters and signature match the desired fluent
      Returns:
      a compiled fluent defined in this problem
      Throws:
      FormatException - if no compiled fluent is defined in this problem
